    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. what about algorithms that don't use gradient descent though? like if i'm using k-nearest neighbors or something? does the scale difference mess with those too?",
      "source": "evaluator",
      "targeted_response_start": "",
      "beast_baseline": "that makes sense. what about algorithms that don't use gradient descent though? like if i'm using k-nearest neighbors or something? does the scale difference mess with those too?",
